Language.name: nl
Language.Field: De camping ligt ca. 1 km ten westen van het centrum van Andau. Vanuit Andau via de B206 richting Tadten. Even buiten de bebouwde kom van Andau ligt de camping rechts aan deze weg.

Vlak terrein bij een recreatiegebied. De toeristische standplaatsen bevinden zich op twee langgerekte, rechthoekige grasvelden die van elkaar gescheiden zijn door de vaste standplaatsen. Het terrein is begroeid met struiken en bomen. De camping grenst aan een recreatiemeertje met ligweide en zwemgelegenheid. In Burgenland zijn fietsroutes uitgezet.

Het grind/grasstrand aan de Pusztasee meet 5 bij 200 m. Daggasten zijn welkom, honden niet toegestaan. Het water in het meertje loopt vrij snel af tot een diepte van 15 m. In het water drijven drie opblaasbare eilanden. Via een trapje kan men het water in.

Language.name: nl
Language.Field: De camping ligt ca. 1 km ten zuidwesten van het centrum van Donnerskirchen. Vanuit Donnerskirchen via de B15 richting Mannersdorf. Na ca. 1,5 km linksaf. Dan nog ca. 400 m tot de camping.

De camping, aan de rand van het dorp, maakt deel uit van een groot sportcomplex met tennisbanen, minigolf en een voor kampeerders gratis toegankelijk groot zwembad met waterglijbaan. De standplaatsen bevinden zich zowel op een kleine weide als hoger gelegen op terrassen met bomen. Dit zorgt ook voor het verschil in beschutting, die varieert van geen tot voldoende. De standplaatsen zijn niet afgebakend.

Language.name: nl
Language.Field: De camping ligt 1 km ten noorden van Jennersdorf en wordt aangegeven.

Het rechthoekige, vlakke campingterrein kenmerkt zich door speels aangelegde kampeervelden en verharde wegen. De standplaatsen, waarvan er veel vast zijn, bevinden zich op gras, grenzend aan straatjes en zijn afgebakend door bomen en struiken. De camping grenst aan het gemeentelijk zwembad, dat voor kampeerders niet gratis toegankelijk is.

Language.name: nl
Language.Field: De camping ligt ten noorden van Postojna. In Postojna de borden naar de grotten 'Postojnska Jama' volgen. Vervolgens richting Predjamski Grad en de campingborden volgen. De laatste 2,5 km is bochtig en gaat omhoog.

Natuurcamping met standplaatsen rond het zwembad en op kleine terrasjes verspreid over de heuvels en dalen van het terrein. Ook zijn bungalows te huur. Het terrein ligt boven de Pivkagrot, waarvan de ingang op 8 km ligt. Vanaf de camping lopen wandel- en fietsroutes. Het centrum van Postojna ligt op 5 km.

Language.name: nl
Language.Field: De camping ligt in het centrum van Ankaran, aan zee. A1 (Ljubljana-Koper) afrit Ankaran. In Ankaran campingborden volgen.

Deze camping ligt deels op een helling onder loof- en naaldbomen, met een grote variatie aan subtropische planten, en deels op kale weiden. Op hetzelfde terrein ligt ook een hotel- en bungalowcomplex.
Het 500 m lange strand is gemaakt van betonplaten. Er zijn een zwemsteiger, een zwemeiland en een deels verharde ligweide. Het strand is toegankelijk voor dagtoeristen.
Op het terrein is een wellnesscentrum met een overdekt zwembad, dit is ook toegankelijk voor daggasten. Ook is er een bowlingbaan.
De plaatsen bij het water zijn vooral bestemd voor seizoenskampeerders en verhuuraccommodaties.
Overdag en soms 's nachts merkbaar geluid

Language.name: nl
Language.Field: De camping ligt 800 meter ten zuiden van Bovec aan de doorgaande weg. In verband met een bergpas van 14% en haarspeldbochten, op de wegen 203 en 206, is het voor caravans beter om via udine (Italie) te rijden.

Vanaf de onder loofbomen liggende standplaatsen is uitzicht op de Julische Alpen. Deze vlakke camping bevindt zich op 5 minuten lopen van Bovec. De rivier is geschikt voor vissers. Naast de ingang van de ligt een restaurant. Kampeerders kunnen gebruikmaken van lockers en een koelkast.
De camping biedt in georganiseerd verband watersportactiviteiten aan, zoals rafting, kano- en kajaktochten.

Language.name: nl
Language.Field: De camping ligt 2 km ten noordoosten van Mojstrana. Na de Karawankentunnel afrit Jesenice/Hrusica nemen, daarna via weg 202 richting Kranjskra Gora. Na ca. 4 km ligt de camping ter hoogte van het gehucht Dovje aan de rechterkant van deze weg.
Gezinscamping met veel terrassen en aparte veldjes voor tenten. De standplaatsen liggen onder diverse loof- en naaldbomen en hebben uitzicht op de bergen.
De omgeving leent zich goed voor bergwandelingen en mountainbiketochten. Het Nationaal Park Triglav bevindt zich op 1 km.
Er komt een nieuw tweede sanitairgebouw.

Language.Field: De camping ligt 3 km ten zuidwesten van Recica ob Savinji. Weg 225 (Mozirje-Gornji Grad) na Mozirje afslag Nazarje, 200 m na de brug over de Savinja rechtsaf. Na 3 km in het dorp Sp. Pobrezje rechtsaf, 400 m smalle weg naar camping.

Language.Field: De camping ligt 1 km ten westen van Duplje. A2 (Karawankentunnel - Ljubljana), afrit Naklo en de borden Duplje volgen. Ter hoogte van Duplje linksaf en ca. 800 m een halfverharde smalle doodlopende weg volgen.

De kleinschalige camping ligt in een landelijke omgeving, bij een oude watermolen. De standplaatsen bevinden zich tussen de rivier en de receptie met woonhuis op een deels schaduwrijk, deels open vlak terrein met bomen. Vanaf de camping starten volop wandel- en fietsroutes.
De gastvrouw kookt naar wens op afspraak.

Language.Field: De camping ligt 1 km ten zuiden van Lendava. In de stad voor de brug over de Lendava rechtsaf richting Terme Lendava en Hotel/Camping Lipa. De receptie is in het hotel.

Het terrein maakt deel uit van een thermaal hotelcomplex en ligt naast het bad. De standplaatsen liggen op kleine grasveldjes met weinig schaduw. Douches voor dames en heren zijn niet gescheiden. De ecocamping ligt direct aan de wildstromende rivier de Soca. Vanaf de camping is er panoramisch zicht op de omliggende bergen. Language.name: nl
Language.Field: De camping ligt 2 km ten westen van Soca. Vanaf Bovec weg 206 richting Kranska Gora. Na ca. 8 km rechtsaf. De camping volgt na 200 m.

De rustige camping ligt hoog boven de rivier de Soca in een breed dal. Vanaf elke plek is er panoramisch zicht op de omringende bergwereld van het Nationale Park Triglav. Loofbomen zorgen voor schaduw. Het gehele terrein is opgesierd met kleurige bloemperken. Er zijn barbecues voor campinggasten in bruikleen.

Field_Conf.Label: service_point_waste_water_tanks
Field_Conf.Extended_Description: Possibility for emptying waste water tanks (easy access and handling, stable ground). Explanatory comments: Sometimes connected with a camper service station. Either at the campsite or immediately outside.

Field_Conf.Label: full_camper_service_station
Field_Conf.Extended_Description: Possibility for emptying waste water and faecal tanks (easy access and handling, stable ground) and refilling the fresh water tank. Either at the campsite or immediately outside.

Field_Conf.Label: cooking
Field_Conf.Extended_Description: Gas, electric, 2 cookers with two flames.

Field_Conf.Label: total_campsite_area
Field_Conf.Extended_Description: The surface of the entire grounds expressed in ha. Explanatory comments: For example, if part of an estate or recreational park, the surface is only that area that is used as a campsite.

Field_Conf.Label: mean_sea_level
Field_Conf.Extended_Description: The (average) number of meters above sea level at which the campsite lies.

Field_Conf.Label: residential_pitches
Field_Conf.Extended_Description: The number of pitches that are not available for tourists in the high season. Explanatory comments: Camping guests include any travelling companions using the same pitch. The exact numbers of residential pitches must be given (from the owner) whereever they are. The inspecter checks always only the plausibility.

Field_Conf.Label: CEE_hook_ups_number
Field_Conf.Extended_Description: Min and max ampere. Explanatory comments: The total number of electrical outlets may not exceed the number of pitches for tourists.

Field_Conf.Label: conventional_hook_ups_number
Field_Conf.Extended_Description: Min and max ampere. Explanatory comments: The total number of electrical outlets may not exceed the number of pitches for tourists.

Field_Conf.Label: number_tv_socket
Field_Conf.Extended_Description: Explanatory comment: At the tourist pitches.

Field_Conf.Label: gas_connections
Field_Conf.Extended_Description: It must be possible to connect directly to a central gas facility.

Field_Conf.Label: pitch_related_sanitary_cabins
Field_Conf.Extended_Description: Combined sanitary facilities at the pitch that the camping guest can rent for his/her own use when at the campsite. Explanatory comments: Pitch-related sanitary cabins lower the pressure to the "normal" sanitary facilities. Thus for the calculation of the quantity score these cabins are deducted from the total amount of tourists.

Field_Conf.Label: specially_pitches_for_camping_cars_inside
Field_Conf.Extended_Description: A pitch inside of the campsite that has a stable surface and is specially made for a camping car. Explanatory comment: Clearly indicated, stable underground, easy accessibility, short stay (one or some overnights). Normally these pitches are located in the entrance region immediately after the barrier of the campsite.

Field_Conf.Label: specially_pitches_for_camping_cars_outside
Field_Conf.Extended_Description: A pitch outside of the campsite that has a stable surface and is specially made for a camping car. Explanatory comment: Normally these pitches are clearly indicated (as overnight places) and fully equiped (combi-tab for fresh and waste water, electricity). Parking and wating places for late arrivals do not fulfill the criterias.

Field_Conf.Label: view_of_the_campsite

Field_Conf.Label: calmness_of_the_campsite
Field_Conf.ParamA: day and night always calm=>day and night always calm at least at night calm=>at least at night calm day always, night sometimes noisy=>day always, night sometimes noisy day and night always noisy=>day and night always noisy

Field_Conf.Label: text_picture_campsite
Field_Conf.Extended_Description: in principal: characteristic of the campsite including its surrounding (visible, hearable, sniffable, perceptible); catchwords: structure of the ground, shape and vegetation of the terrain in general / characteristic of the pitches for tourists / if necessary information about negative influence from residential and rental parts / if applicable description of dominant and special things (e.g. big leisure time facilities at the entrance) / in rare cases also link to POIs (e.g. Pont du Gard)

Field_Conf.Label: snack_bar_snack_stand
Field_Conf.Extended_Description: A snack bar is a place where simple, fast-food comestibles and/or meals are available/can be taken away. It may have a waiting area and/or a sitting area indoors or outdoors. Explanatory comments: Fried products, hot dogs, sausages. Available + opening period or distance

Field_Conf.Label: fridge
Field_Conf.Extended_Description: Possibility to rent a fridge.

Field_Conf.Label: take_away
Field_Conf.Extended_Description: A take-away meal is a (to be ordered) full, warm meal prepared and served by a place to eat at least 5 days a week in the high season and that is meant to be eaten elsewhere. Available and opening period.

Field_Conf.Label: kiosk
Field_Conf.Extended_Description: There is a small assortment of provisions including (to be ordered) fresh bread and perhaps some non-food articles. Explanatory comments: This can be an actual shop or part of, for example, the reception desk or simply a (outdoor) booth. Examples of extra articles include ice cream, soft drinks, sweets, newspapers and magazines. With indication of opening period.

Field_Conf.Label: grocery
Field_Conf.Extended_Description: if yes, then distance for this element can't be filled.

Field_Conf.Label: supermarket
Field_Conf.Extended_Description: In principal the complete catalogue of a "good" grocery (see above) but of larger assortment including fresh bread and fresh meal. Explanatory comments: There are shopping trolleys and baskets, at least 2 cash boxes and a clear route from the entry to the exit. There are clearly indicated long opening hours (min. 8 hours/day with 6 days/week in July and August). Available + opening period or distance.

Field_Conf.Label: camping_leisure_items
Field_Conf.Extended_Description: A basic supply of both leisure time and camping articles. Explanatory comment: For example, swimming caps, water wings, tent guys and pegs, gas, etc. Available + opening period or distance.

Field_Conf.Label: outdoor_playground
Field_Conf.Extended_Description: A playground is a separated part of the grounds in which with at least four different pieces of playground equipment suitable for children up to 12 are grouped together.

Field_Conf.Label: indoor_playground
Field_Conf.Extended_Description: A playing area with at least 3 different pieces of equipment for physical activity in a separate area or room. With indication of size. Explanatory comments: This may also be one piece of equipment that offers three different ways of playing.

Field_Conf.Label: adventure_playground
Field_Conf.Extended_Description: There are at least 3 pieces of playground equipment that demand survival skills. With indication of size. Explanatory comments: The playground can be indoors or outdoors. The playground equipment offers challenges and demands some skill and a certain amount of courage from the user. Examples of equipment: rope ladder, climbing wall, cable lift.

Field_Conf.Label: tennis_court
Field_Conf.Extended_Description: A court of (what appears to be) the customary size, that is fenced in and has a a net and lines for a single and a double game. Explanatory comments: Tiled surface is not acceptable. Half court is not considered a tennis court. Available or distance.

Field_Conf.Label: covered_tennis_court
Field_Conf.Extended_Description: An indoor tennis court of (what appears to be) the customary size and that has a net and lines for a single and a double game. Available or distance.

Field_Conf.Label: multi_functional_sport_field
Field_Conf.Extended_Description: A multi-sports area is a closed-off sports area with a hard surface that can easily be rearranged for a number of sports. Explanatory comments: Often in the form of a (indoor) soccer cage where, for example, basketball can also be played.

Field_Conf.Label: finnish_sauna
Field_Conf.Extended_Description: A sauna is a wooden cabin in which the temperature is increased so that the body begins to sweat. There are also facilities for cooling off, such as a cold shower and/or a plunge bath.

Field_Conf.Label: earth_sauna
Field_Conf.Extended_Description: A sauna is a wooden cabin in which the temperature is increased so that the body begins to sweat. There are also facilities for cooling off, such as a cold shower and/or a plunge bath.

Field_Conf.Label: bio_sauna
Field_Conf.Extended_Description: A sauna is a wooden cabin in which the temperature is increased so that the body begins to sweat. There are also facilities for cooling off, such as a cold shower and/or a plunge bath.

Field_Conf.Label: steam_bath
Field_Conf.Extended_Description: A steam bath is a room in which steam is produced so that it becomes very warm. There is equipment to increase the humidity to such an extent that mist is caused because the dew point is exceeded. Explanatory comments: It resembles a sauna but, because the humidity is much higher than in a sauna, the real temperature is not as warm although it feels just as warm.

Field_Conf.Label: whirlpool
Field_Conf.Extended_Description: A bubble bath/ whirlpool/jacuzzi is a large bath with a number of places to sit or lie and that has warm water and massaging streams of water. There are jets in the bath through which strong streams of water and air are pumped. These streams of water massage the body.

Field_Conf.Label: solarium
Field_Conf.Extended_Description: A solarium consists of an electric sunbed that can be made of 1 or 2 parts. The one-piece sunbed is also called a sunbed.

Field_Conf.Label: fitness_room
Field_Conf.Extended_Description: A fitness room is a separate room with at least three different pieces of fitness equipment.

Field_Conf.Label: recreation_bad_weather_room
Field_Conf.Extended_Description: A separate area or room furnished as a sitting area that can be used only for recreational purposes or in bad weather and in which guests are not obliged to buy something to eat or drink. Explanatory comments: The area has, for example, a TV, books, games, etc. Sometimes it could be combined with cooking facilities.

Field_Conf.Label: miniclub
Field_Conf.Extended_Description: A miniclub is a handicrafts/activity programme for children up to 6 years old that is led by specially assigned personnel. This activity takes place in a separate inside area at a previously scheduled time for at least one hour per week and for at least 4 weeks in July and August. Explanatory comments: The miniclub itself is an additional symbol which has a higher threshold. Offers from the miniclub (=0-6) are assigned to activity programme for kids under 12.

Field_Conf.Label: target_group_naturists
Field_Conf.Extended_Description: see separate list

Field_Conf.Label: outdoor_pool
Field_Conf.Extended_Description: An outdoor pool is outdoors and consists of one or more concrete or durable synthetic basins sunk into the ground and filled with water. There are permanent facilities. An outdoor pool can also be a pool whose roof can be open or closed. A (semi-permanent) above-ground basin is NOT considered to be a swimming pool Always: size (sqm, m x m, diameter) and opening period. Minimum depth: > 60 cm. If applicable, public access in high and low season. Explanatory comments: Indicate semi-permanent roofing in the text. A splashing pool at a slide or a whirlpool are not basins and are not calculated as part of the surface area.

Field_Conf.Label: outdoor_pool_with_flexible_roof
Field_Conf.Extended_Description: An outdoor pool is outdoors and consists of one or more concrete or durable synthetic basins sunk into the ground and filled with water. There are permanent facilities. An outdoor pool can also be a pool whose roof can be open or closed. A (semi-permanent) above-ground basin is NOT considered to be a swimming pool Always: size (sqm, m x m, diameter) and opening period. Minimum depth: > 60 cm. If applicable, public access in high and low season. Explanatory comments: Indicate semi-permanent roofing in the text. A splashing pool at a slide or a whirlpool are not basins and are not calculated as part of the surface area.

Field_Conf.Label: outdoor_pool_with_public_access
Field_Conf.Extended_Description: An outdoor pool is outdoors and consists of one or more concrete or durable synthetic basins sunk into the ground and filled with water. There are permanent facilities. An outdoor pool can also be a pool whose roof can be open or closed. A (semi-permanent) above-ground basin is NOT considered to be a swimming pool Always: size (sqm, m x m, diameter) and opening period. Minimum depth: > 60 cm. If applicable, public access in high and low season. Explanatory comments: Indicate semi-permanent roofing in the text. A splashing pool at a slide or a whirlpool are not basins and are not calculated as part of the surface area.

Field_Conf.Label: indoor_pool
Field_Conf.Extended_Description: An indoor pool is indoors and consists of one or more concrete or durable synthetic basins sunk into the ground and filled with water. There are permanent facilities. Pools with flexible roof are always considered as outdoor pools. Always: size (sqm, m x m, diameter) and opening period. Minimum depth: > 60 cm. If applicable, public access in high and low season. Explanatory comments: A splashing pool at a slide or a whirlpool are not basins and are not calculated as part of the surface area.

Field_Conf.Label: indoor_pool_with_flexible_roof
Field_Conf.Extended_Description: An indoor pool is indoors and consists of one or more concrete or durable synthetic basins sunk into the ground and filled with water. There are permanent facilities. Pools with flexible roof are always considered as outdoor pools. Always: size (sqm, m x m, diameter) and opening period. Minimum depth: > 60 cm. If applicable, public access in high and low season. Explanatory comments: A splashing pool at a slide or a whirlpool are not basins and are not calculated as part of the surface area.

Field_Conf.Label: paddling_pool_outdoor_1
Field_Conf.Extended_Description: A paddling pool is a separate water-filled basin and that is physically separated from the other basin(s) or has a proper separation. A (semi-permanent) above-ground basin, inflatable or made from a do-it-yourself kit is NOT considered to be a paddling pool. Always: size (sqm, m x m, diameter) and opening period. Maximum depth: < 60 cm.

Field_Conf.Label: paddling_area_outdoor
Field_Conf.Extended_Description: A paddling area is always connected to a bigger pool (indoor/outdoor) with only a visible separation like a rope, a chain with floaters or a wall/threshold as high as the level of the water. Maximum depth: < 60 cm. Explanatory comments: The size and quality evaluation is always to be considered together with the bigger pool.

Field_Conf.Label: water_chute
Field_Conf.Extended_Description: A water slide is a slide designed especially for a lake, swimming pool (indoor/outdoor) or splash pool that has water flowing down its slope. Explanatory comments: The form and size of these slides differ from simpler slides in a playground since they often have spectacular forms, heights or lengths.

Field_Conf.Label: fun_adventure_pool
Field_Conf.Extended_Description: A pool with multiple bassins in different shapes (could also be connected to a large bassin) where the emphasis is on playful elements and where there is equipment to play with. Additional various outstanding facilities like bridges, lagoons, floating channels, multiple curled slides, cascades.... Explanatory comments: A subquestion to indoor/outdoor pool.

Field_Conf.Label: indoor_pool_distance
Field_Conf.Extended_Description: A public pool at a maximum of 10 km from the campsite that camping guests can use. No details about size and opening period. Only free entrance for campers' will be mentioned in the tariffs.

Field_Conf.Label: distance_sea_with_swimming
Field_Conf.Extended_Description: The number of km to the sea with possibility to swim.

Field_Conf.Label: distance_lake_with_swimming
Field_Conf.Extended_Description: The number of km to the lake with possibility to swim.

Field_Conf.Label: distance_river_with_swimming
Field_Conf.Extended_Description: The number of km to the river with possibility to swim.

Field_Conf.Label: directly_adjacent_beach_sea
Field_Conf.Extended_Description: Always size (sqm, m x m, diameter). Explanatory comments: The lenght of the beach is never higher than the length of the adjacent campsite terrain. Definition of directly: 0m distance or max. 50m if there are no other obstacles than e.g. a foot- or bikeway or in case of a street a bridge resp. tunnel is necessary.

Field_Conf.Label: ground_of_the_beach_sea
Field_Conf.Extended_Description: This is the beach at the sea directly adjacent or in distance.

Field_Conf.Label: directly_adjacent_beach_lake
Field_Conf.Extended_Description: Always size (sqm, m x m, diameter). Explanatory comments: The lenght of the beach is never higher than the length of the adjacent campsite terrain. Definition of directly: 0m distance or max. 50m if there are no other obstacles than e.g. a foot- or bikeway or in case of a street a bridge resp. tunnel is necessary.

Field_Conf.Label: text_beach
Field_Conf.Extended_Description: size (max. length and width of the directly adjacent terrain) / definition of directly: 0m distance or max. 50m if there are no other obstacles than e.g. a foot- or bikeway (in that case we inform what's exactly in between) or in case of a street a bridge resp. tunnel is necessary / structure of the ground / if applicable e.g. water chute, diving board or diving tower, wooden pier, swimming island / specialities about the access to the beach (e.g. steps) or into the water (e.g. ladder) / public access to the beach through the campsite; beachvolleyball and FKK will be mentioned in this text only by ANWB

Field_Conf.Label: rental_tents
Field_Conf.Extended_Description: Camping equipment consisting of a construction that has a roof and walls of canvas and that provides shelter for one or more guests during their stay at the campsite. Explanatory comments: Only number of tents, including tour operators. The constructions are very divers: bungalow tents, De Waard tents, tepees, tree tents, etc.

Field_Conf.Label: rental_caravans
Field_Conf.Extended_Description: Mobile camping equipment including a trailer that is suitable for habitation.

Field_Conf.Label: rental_mobile_homes_chalets
Field_Conf.Extended_Description: A pre-fabricated holiday home with own sanitary facilities and cooking facilities.

Field_Conf.Label: rental_bungalows
Field_Conf.Extended_Description: A holiday home (solid building) built on a foundation at the campsite with own sanitary facilities and cooking facilities.

Field_Conf.Label: rental_cabins
Field_Conf.Extended_Description: A (wooden) holiday accommodation that is built on a foundation at the campsite, no sanitary facilities.

Field_Conf.Label: rental_miscellaneous
Field_Conf.Extended_Description: Meant here are rental accommodations that do not fall into the above categories (e.g. apartments, pipo wagons). Not rooms or group accommodations.

Field_Conf.Extended_Description: s.e. (automatically calculated)
